    "created_at": "2015-10-13T20:23:27Z",
    "updated_at": "2015-10-13T20:23:27Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "I created my own replay with a disconnection via timeout by starting 3 clients locally (one under a debugger) and running a game. I paused in the debugger to force one client to disconnect via a timeout due to \"lag\".\n\nI can confirm this PR fixed the replays from the perspective of the players that continued the game (which would otherwise freeze without this PR).\n\nThe replay of the player who was disconnected was interesting. It also no longer freezes and continues! The game desyncs from reality at this point but keeps going regardless - the replay just happily continues past 100%. No crashes or anything. Some of the units were fighting and continued their attacks - but not in the way the real game played out obviously.\n\nThat probably shouldn't happen :)\n"
  },
